#ROOM
Vnum     26018
Name     &MThe Road West&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     The road continues westward, cutting through dense, ancient groves.
Majestic Strigid Owls watch you silently from the high branches.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    26014
Desc      Dolanaar.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    26016
Desc      The Barrow Den.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    26019
Desc      Lake Al'Ameth.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26004 2 26018
  Reset E 1 26003 10 17
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26019
Name     &CLake Al'Ameth&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A crystal clear, placid lake situated in the center of the world tree.
The water is incredibly refreshing. Small boats are tied to a wooden
dock on the western shore.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    26018
Desc      The road to Dolanaar.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    26020
Desc      The Oracle Glade.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26020
Name     &MThe Oracle Glade&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     A deeply magical, secluded glade. Ancient dryads and keepers of the grove
often gather here to discuss the health of the world tree. The air hums
with a soothing, restorative energy.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    26019
Desc      Lake Al'Ameth.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    26022
Desc      The Wellspring River.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26021
Name     &MStarbreeze Village - Center&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The corruption is palpable here. Gnarlpine Shamans chant twisted spells,
burning the once-beautiful Elven architecture. They attack any outsiders
on sight.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    26010
Desc      The outskirts.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26008 2 26021
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26022
Name     &CThe Wellspring River&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A rushing, shallow river that feeds the various lakes and moonwells of
Teldrassil. Following it north leads into a dark, foreboding stretch of
woods where the corruption is thickest.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    26020
Desc      The Oracle Glade.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    26023
Desc      The Twisted Glade.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26023
Name     &dThe Twisted Glade&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     The trees here are completely dead, their bark blackened and rotting.
Disgusting clumps of Fel Moss slither across the ground, attacking anything
that breathes. The source of the corruption is near.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    26022
Desc      The river.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    26024
Desc      A dark cave entrance.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26013 2 26023
  Reset G 1 26011 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26024
Name     &dCave of Lord Melenas - Entrance&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The stench of sulfur and decay is overwhelming. The corruption that threatens
the entire world tree flows from this very cave. The jagged rocks look
like the teeth of a massive demon.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    26023
Desc      The Twisted Glade.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    26025
Desc      Enter the demonic lair.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26013 2 26024
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26025
Name     &dCave of Lord Melenas - Lair&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    dark indoors~
Desc     The heart of the rot. Lord Melenas, a cruel and twisted satyr, commands
the corruption from this dark chamber. He seeks to poison the roots of
Teldrassil entirely on behalf of the Burning Legion.
~
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    26024
Desc      The entrance.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 26014 1 26025
  Reset G 1 26014 10
  Reset G 1 26013 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26026
Name     &MThe Road to Darnassus&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     Leaving the wilder parts of the forest behind, the path becomes paved
with smooth, glowing stones. The immense pink glow of the capital city
can be seen shining through the trees ahead.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    26019
Desc      Lake Al'Ameth.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    26028
Desc      The Darnassus Approach.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    26027
Desc      The path to Rut'theran.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26027
Name     &MRut'theran Path&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     This winding trail leads to the glowing portal that connects Teldrassil
to the small village of Rut'theran at the base of the world tree, allowing
passage to the mainland of Kalimdor.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    26026
Desc      The road to Darnassus.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26028
Name     &MDarnassus Approach&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The trees part, revealing the breathtaking architecture of the Night Elf
capital. Elaborate bridges cross glowing streams, and the majestic Temple
of the Moon dominates the skyline.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    26026
Desc      The forest road.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    26029
Desc      The gates of the city.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     26029
Name     &MThe Gates of Darnassus&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You stand before the magnificent, glowing gates of Darnassus. Elite
Sentinels stand guard, welcoming allies of the Alliance while keeping a
vigilant watch for any signs of Horde intrusion. The glory of the Night
Elves awaits within.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    26028
Desc      The approach.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    11800
Desc      Enter the Tradesmen's Terrace.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ENDAREA
